misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No misconception detected (correct linear search with early exit)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that initializing an index to -1 and scanning left-to-right until a match is found (or the end is reached) correctly yields the first occurrence index, and printing -1 indicates “not found.”
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap: in Java, array elements are accessed by index; the loop condition `i<n && y==-1` correctly stops after the first match, preserving the first-occurrence requirement. If no match occurs, `y` remains -1.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None; produces correct output for all standard cases including “not found.”
